        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(matrix): guard JSON.parse against malformed homeserver response bodies",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n`extensions/matrix/src/matrix/sdk/http-client.ts:55` calls `JSON.parse(text)` on the Matrix homeserver response body without try/catch. Malformed JSON → unhandled SyntaxError.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `extensions/matrix/src/matrix/sdk/http-client.ts`: wrap `JSON.parse(text)` in try/catch → `Error(\"malformed JSON\")` with `statusCode`\n- `extensions/matrix/src/matrix/sdk/http-client.test.ts`: test verifying malformed JSON → Error\n- `test/_proof_matrix_json_guard.mts`: **v3** — real HTTP server + `MatrixAuthedHttpClient` with `ssrfPolicy: { allowPrivateNetwork: true }` to bypass loopback SSRF\n\nLabel: bugfix | merge-risk: 🟢 minimal | AI-assisted\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Real HTTP proof — MatrixAuthedHttpClient.requestJson (L2, v3 SSRF-bypassed)\n\n```\n$ node --import tsx test/_proof_matrix_json_guard.mts\n\n[proof] malformed JSON server on :XXXXX\nPASS  malformed JSON: throws Error :: type=Error\nPASS  malformed JSON: mentions malformed JSON :: msg=\"Matrix homeserver returned malformed JSON\"\nPASS  malformed JSON: has statusCode :: statusCode=200\nPASS  valid JSON: parsed correctly :: result={\"user_id\":\"@test:matrix.org\"}\nPASS  non-JSON content type: returns text unchanged :: result=\"pong\"\n\n[proof] 5 PASS, 0 FAIL\n```\n\n### Unit test\n\n```\npnpm exec vitest run extensions/matrix/src/matrix/sdk/http-client.test.ts\n ✓ MatrixAuthedHttpClient > throws descriptive error on malformed JSON success response\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n```\n\n### Fix history\n- v1: unit test only → `silver shellfish`\n- v2: +proof script → SSRF blocked\n- **v3**: lint fix (`String()` removal) + `ssrfPolicy: { allowPrivateNetwork: true }` to bypass loopback SSRF in proof",
